<subSubSection id="C33C6549CA70FF9FCD9537EAFA7FF28A" pageId="32" pageNumber="651" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B9936C2CA70FF9FCD9537EAFA7FF28A" blockId="32.[2030,2617,2806,3232]" lastBlockId="32.[1416,2616,3238,3467]" pageId="32" pageNumber="651">
<emphasis id="B952EAD0CA70FF9FCD9537EAF76BF39F" box="[2032,2285,3042,3075]" pageId="32" pageNumber="651">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body 
<quantity id="4CDE9B27CA70FF9FC3C337EAF5B7F39F" box="[2470,2609,3042,3075]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.45" metricValueMax="2.9" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="32" pageNumber="651" unit="cm" value="24.5" valueMax="29.0" valueMin="20.0">20-29 cm</quantity>
, tail 
<quantity id="4CDE9B27CA70FF9FC2573019F747F3B6" box="[2098,2241,3089,3114]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.55" metricValueMax="1.8" metricValueMin="1.3" pageId="32" pageNumber="651" unit="cm" value="15.5" valueMax="18.0" valueMin="13.0">13-18 cm</quantity>
; weight 
<quantity id="4CDE9B27CA70FF9FC32B3019F660F3B6" box="[2382,2534,3089,3114]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="2.05" metricValueMax="2.6" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="32" pageNumber="651" unit="g" value="205.0" valueMax="260.0" valueMin="150.0">150-260 g</quantity>
. The Yellow-bellied Weasel has a long, slender body and short limbs. The upperparts are dark chocolate to rusty brown; the underparts are pale yellow or light orange-brown. The chin and upper lip are whitish. The tail is bushy and the same color as the upperparts. Some white patches may occur on the feet.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33C6549CA70FF9FCFED3114F80CF217" pageId="32" pageNumber="651" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="8B9936C2CA70FF9FCFED3114F80CF217" blockId="32.[1416,2616,3238,3467]" pageId="32" pageNumber="651">
<emphasis id="B952EAD0CA70FF9FCFED3114FA71F2A1" box="[1416,1527,3356,3389]" pageId="32" pageNumber="651">Habitat.</emphasis>
Pine forests, up to 
<quantity id="4CDE9B27CA70FF9FCD613114F8EFF2A1" box="[1796,1897,3356,3389]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="32" pageNumber="651" unit="m" value="4000.0">4000 m</quantity>
(above the timber line). In Western Himalaya from 
<quantity id="4CDE9B27CA70FF9FCFEC314BF9BAF2F8" box="[1417,1596,3395,3428]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.1" metricValueMax="5.2" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="32" pageNumber="651" unit="m" value="4100.0" valueMax="5200.0" valueMin="3000.0">3000-5200 m</quantity>
in the cold deserts, but in 
<collectingCountry id="F3317652CA70FF9FCDAF314BF7F7F2F8" box="[1994,2161,3395,3428]" name="Hong Kong" pageId="32" pageNumber="651">Hong Kong</collectingCountry>
found in much lower altitudes, from close to sea-level to over 
<specimenCount id="9D20FD4BCA70FF9FCD4B3162F80CF217" box="[1838,1930,3434,3467]" pageId="32" pageNumber="651" type="generic">
<quantity id="4CDE9B27CA70FF9FCD4B3162F803F217" box="[1838,1925,3434,3467]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="32" pageNumber="651" unit="m" value="200.0">200 m</quantity>
.
</specimenCount>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33C6549CA71FF9ECAA23D25FEC1FEF1" pageId="33" pageNumber="652" type="food_feeding">
<paragraph id="8B9936C2CA71FF9ECAA23D25FEC1FEF1" blockId="33.[197,1401,299,680]" pageId="33" pageNumber="652">
<emphasis id="B952EAD0CA71FF9ECAA23D25FE56FEDA" box="[199,464,301,326]" pageId="33" pageNumber="652">Food and Feeding.</emphasis>
Diet is said to include rodents, birds, eggs, lizards, frogs, insects, and fruit.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
